<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 137 
                    The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom (
                        Winant
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d137</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">137</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-12T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-12T16:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–1245:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 137 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-12T17:00:00-04:00">July 12, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5701. For the Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Yesterday we had an oral inquiry from <persName corresp="#p_H1">Halifax</persName> concerning the day on which the President and the
                    Secretary would arrive at <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi>. <persName corresp="#p_H1">Halifax</persName> explained that the Prime Minister and
                        <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> wished to time their departure in
                    such a way as to arrive on the same day as the President and the Secretary.</p>
                <p>We communicated with the Secretary and have now been informed that the present
                    schedule is arranged to permit arrival at <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi>
                    about 3 p.m. local time Sunday, July 15. The Secretary asked that we inform you
                    of this. We have informed <persName corresp="#p_H1">Halifax</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HJD1">J[ohn] D H[ickerson]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
